Coffee Cake
via Judy Heumann

Batter

1 1/2 cups flour
2 tsp baking powder
1/2 tsp salt
1/2 cup sugar
1/4 cup shortening (or butter)
1 egg, beaten
1/2 cup milk (or sour cream)
1 tsp vanilla

Topping Mixture

1/2 cup brown sugar
(2 tbsp flour)
(1/8 tsp salt)
1 tsp cinnamon
(3 tbsp butter)

Topping: Combine everything but the butter in a bowl, and cut in butter.  Mix
until mixture resembles fine crumbs.

Batter: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.  Cut in shortening
(or butter).  Stir in egg, milk, and vanilla.

Spread half of batter in a greased 8" or 9" square baking dish.  Cover with
half of the topping.  Spoon remaining batter over crumb mixture.  Cover with
remaining topping.

Bake at 375F for 25 to 30 minutes.  Serves nine.

